You can define the `timezone_bumper` function as follows:
```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt, bump = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        error("Input must be of DateTime type.")
    end

    return dt + hours(bump)
end
```
This function checks if the input is a `DateTime`. If not, it throws an error. Otherwise, it adds the specified number of hours to the timestamp and returns the result.
